</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-EROOM foKNLL pf-38_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-39_"><strong>Our rights</strong> - Reinforce the need to understand, protect, and claim our rights as defined by the UDHR.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-41_"><strong>Our future</strong> - Acknowledges the link between human rights and sustainable progress for future generations.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-43_"><strong>Right now</strong> - Calls for immediate action to confront pressing human rights issues like inequality, poverty, and environmental injustice.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-45_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-46_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-47_">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-EROOM foKNLL pf-49_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-50_">Over 160 million children globally are engaged in child labour, with many in hazardous conditions (International Labour Organization, 2024).</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-52_">Women earn 23% less than men globally for the same work (UN Women, 2024).
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-54_">It is estimated that over 27 million people are victims of modern slavery today (Walk Free Foundation, 2024).
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-56_">Developing countries bear 80% of the burden of climate change impacts yet contribute the least to global emissions (United Nations Environment Programme, 2024).
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-58_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-59_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-60_">The importance of Human Rights today</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS ckDBXz pf-62_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-c19c440c-5577-4cc8-bce8-b7e44a3c3a7f"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Human rights are more than ideals; they are the foundation for dignity, equality, and justice. They protect against abuse, promote societal harmony, and enable individuals to thrive. By acting now, we can address systemic issues, empower communities, and pave the way for a sustainable future where everyone can live with dignity.
